A problem I have encountered, but do not see mentioned in the 
documentation, is that to read chemkin II style mechanisms in matlab 
requires editing the ctbin.m file to reflect the path to where ck2cti.exe 
is located.  This was a problem for me when using the function such as:

 &gt;&gt; g=IdealGasMix(&#39;chem.inp&#39;,&#39;therm.txt&#39;)

The standard text of the ctbin.m m-file looks something like this:

function path = ctbin
path = &#39;c:/cantera/bin&#39;;

The path string needs to be changed to reflect the actual location of 
ck2cti.exe, for example:

path = &#39;d:/program files/cantera154/bin&#39;

or wherever this is located.



